A request from the Editor Feedback Page:

{quote}A side effect of removing wiki markup from Confluence is that we have lost the ability to review documents in Crucible. This was a major feature for us, and a significant factor in choosing Crucible over other code review systems.

What we used to be able to do was to create a review, browse Confluences as a 'repository', and select the pages we wanted to review. If a reviewer had a comment, then in Crucible they could insert that comment right at the lines/paras that the comment applied to - i.e. exactly like source code. It also meant we could review design docs and code alongside each other.{quote}

As noted [here|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CRUCIBLE/Crucible+2.7+Upgrade+Guide] the plugin was unbundled from Crucible 2.7 as it was made to work with Wiki Markup.

To return, a version would need to be created which supported the new Storage Format.

