From Editor Feedback page:

{quote}For an example of what I mean, try turning off the paragraph marks in Word (I'm using 2010), and then selecting some blank paragraphs. Notice how Word highlights the paragraphs, even though they are blank. If you select blank paragraphs in the Confluence rich text editor, then because you have selected something, you no longer see the cursor; however, since the editor does not highlight the selection (the blank paragraphs), you see neither a cursor nor a selection.{quote}

